  "summary": "Inspector Hakast investigates the death of Ina Brent by questioning her colleagues at the Cavendish Typewriting Agency. The supervisor, Miss Martin, suggests that the office staff may have more information due to their tendency to gossip. Hakast speaks with three typists: Janet, a blonde woman; Melanie, a dark-skinned woman; and a third smiling girl.\n\nThe women explain that they realized Ina was missing when she failed to return to the office at two o'clock. They had previously accompanied Ina to a courthouse, but she disappeared following that outing. One colleague recounts learning of Ina's death from a local shopkeeper who mentioned a girl found dead in a phone booth. The women note that Ina had recently seemed preoccupied, making mistakes and acting uncharacteristically distracted, though they add that she did not appear to have a boyfriend. When Hakast asks if Ina was close to Sheila Weber, the women state they were not particularly close and inform him that Sheila is currently at the Curlew Hotel with Professor Puddy.\n\nHakast travels to the Curlew Hotel and interrupts Professor Puddy, who is in the middle of narrating a story to Hilary Weber. Despite the professor's irritation at the interruption, Hakast insists on speaking with Sheila Weber. Upon identifying himself, Hakast informs the professor that the matter concerns the death of Ina Brent, noting a hint of worry in Hilary's eyes.",
